Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks and word embeddings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the effect of different initialization methods on the performance of deep neural networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the use of embeddings in neural networks, which is a common technique in AI research. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper specifically focuses on the effect of initialization methods on the performance of recurrent and convolutional neural networks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with image or video data, but it is still possible as the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks.
